PiperOrigin-RevId: 408036901
Change-Id: I742f2b6af30fa24d9c541baaf43b47416b569e0d","distinct":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tensorflow/tensorflow/commits/c32c22cc9cfb32caf51ce3a207b85e62e7b8c960"},{"sha":"52bad2f3d421fc542e78442f688e676fa7c1405d","author":{"email":"02bd3f004a63c78990e4cfa97922eaaaa6d78ea5@google.com","name":"Dan Moldovan"},"message":"Add a very basic type inference pass, and execute it before before placer.

The pass added in this CL propagates FullType information on a graph's nodes (see NodeDef.experimental_full_type), based on the rules defined for each op's forward type inference function (see OpBuilderWrapper.SetForwardTypeFn). As their name suggests, these functions perform only forward type inference, from arguments to return values.

A future pass could perform a more complete type inference process, one which accounts for the symbolic constraints on types, but that's out of the scope of this change.

While type inference pass may be needed by any process in the compiler chain that relies on type information (as the other passes which add or modify notes may invalidate type information), at present only Placer needs it, so the pass is added as the last pass in the PRE_PLACEMENT to ensure it runs just before Placer.
